    <s:String x:Key="AddCmd_HelpText">How to create a voice command:&#10;&#10;1) Command phrase — the exact word or phrase you say to run the command. Example: comma, new line, undo.&#10;&#10;2) Action type — choose what happens when you say the phrase:&#10;• Type text — types whatever you put in “Action value” (letters, punctuation, symbols).&#10;• Send key — presses a keyboard key or shortcut from “Action value”.&#10;• Change to Persian — switches the keyboard layout to Persian.&#10;• Change to English — switches the keyboard layout to English.&#10;• Delete last words — erases the words you just typed.&#10;&#10;3) Action value — only used by “Type text” and “Send key”:&#10;• Type text: enter the exact text. Examples:  ,  .  ?  or  Best regards&#10;• Send key: a single key or a shortcut. Examples:&#10;   Enter, Tab, Space, Backspace, Delete, Esc, F5&#10;   ^c = Ctrl+C,  ^v = Ctrl+V,  ^z = Ctrl+Z,  ^a = Ctrl+A&#10;   %{F4} = Alt+F4,  %{TAB} = Alt+Tab&#10;   (symbols:  ^ = Ctrl,  % = Alt,  + = Shift)&#10;&#10;Tip: keep each phrase short and distinct so it is recognized reliably.</s:String>

