    <s:String x:Key="Settings_SelectorsHelp">Cloudict recognizes speech by driving the Google Translate web page, so these selectors tell it where the microphone button and the source-text box are. You normally don't need to change them. If recognition or the automatic microphone-reset stops working — e.g. after Google changes the page, or when you switch the typing language — open Google Translate in Chrome, press F12, right-click the microphone (or text) element, choose "Inspect", and copy its identifier (jsname / class / aria-label) into the matching field below.</s:String>
